<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-17T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-17T11:00:00-05:00" n="284" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d284">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6–1745: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-17T19:00:00+03:00">June 17,
                                1945—7 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received June 17—2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2134. Well-informed Soviet source states that there have recently occurred
                        five clashes between Chinese Govt and Chinese Communist forces (to Chungking
                        as 48, repeated Dept as 2134). He says one of these affrays resulted in
                        decisive defeat of one Govt division. We shall appreciate your comment.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>